Many of us greatly liked Erica Klarreich's article



a cyclic group \(\ZZ_p\) which is the additive group \(\{0,1,2,\dots p-1\}\) where the addition occurs "modulo \(p\)" and where the number of elements \(p\) (the "order" of the group) is a prime for the group to be simple. Note that they're Abelian groups.
